HEADWORD: Compartition
<hw>Com`par*ti"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>compartitio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of dividing into parts or
compartments; division; also, a division or compartment.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Their temples . . . needed no <qex>compartitions</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir H. Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Compartment</ent>⟦br⟧
